		<hr size="1">First off, almost all dragon raids, the items are randomed based on the classes that can use them.  So to assume that you are going on a dragon raid and get to roll on some melee or int caster loot is wrong.</P><P>Second lets look at Naggy's loot:<BR>Blight, Hammer of Scourge - not cleric usable, shaman only<BR>Cloak of Flames - all, all - Haste...only melees will get to roll on this.<BR>Gauntlets of Fiery Might - not cleric usable, melee classes only<BR>Gold Plated Koshigatana - not cleric usable, piercing weapon<BR>Heirophant's Crook - not cleric usable, druid only<BR>Orb of Tishan - not cleric usable, int caster and bard only<BR>Red Dragon Scale - used in warrior epic<BR>Selo's Drums of March - not cleric usable, bard only<BR>Bladestopper - cleric usable<BR>Paryers of Life - cleric usable, 5 charges of Word of Healing (I wouldn't want it though)<BR>Red Dragon Tooth - cleric usable, 1 charge of Invoke Death (I wouldn't want it)<BR>Treasure Hunter's Satchel - all, all cleric usable</P><P>So it is greedy to assume that you will get to roll on something meant for another class (at least on my server, that is how it works on dragon raids).</P><P>Don't forget, Naggy drops what?  Up to four items from the above table.</P><P>You should go in there hoping that a Bladestopper or a Treasure Hunter's Satchel drops, as those are the only ones (that are worthwhile for a cleric) you really should get a shot at rolling. Also, the Bladestopper is very much a cleric shield, great AC plus HP, plus more HP from the STA on it.  Guess you don't have your wisdom maxed.</P><P>Sorry, but the tone of your post seems like you are on a high horse.  I assume that you won't ever go on a Fear raid since cleric loot does not drop there.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
