		<hr size="1">I will agree with you on the pick-up dragon raids that the loot usually isn't that fair.  I have been fortuante to be on five consectutive Vox raids and three consecutive Naggy raid where the dragons died on the first attempt.  The same people led each raid, geared mostly for epic weapon items and the other dragon loot is just gravy.</P><P>Back to the Bladestopper...<BR>Baldestopper 25 AC, 15 Sta, 50 HP<BR>Clay Guardian Shield 25 AC, 50 HP<BR>Sarnak Battle Shield 25 AC, 5 Str, 5 Sta, 10 save m/f/c, 40 HP</P><P>I have seen many, many high level clerics (45+) with the Sarnak and Clay shields.  They all have their wisdom maxed out and, and they are then looking for AC and HP.  I would take the Sarnak over the others just for the resists, but I would not pass on the Bladestopper if I didn't have the Sarnak already.</P><P>Granted as a gnome cleric, you might have problems with keeping your wisdom at the 200 mark until you get uber items (I am in the same boat with my Half Elf druid).  So that might be the driving force behind this item not being appealing.</P><P>Your comment..."infact almost all of the time you wont beable to roll on the treasure hunters satchel", I am assuming that since it is 100% wt reduction that monk think they should get it by default.  Personally, all containers should be available for everyone, since we all need to carry stuff and we all have weight problems.  If it only carried large and smaller items, I would have less of a problem, but there are very few giant item, wt reducing bags in the game.</P><P>Pinz 47 dark elf cleric<BR>Pinl 55 half elf druid<BR>Pint 48 halfling warrior<BR><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
